                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A4 Steering Committee/547: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dearing</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-05-21T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 21, 1937—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>15. Legation’s 42, May 20, 10 a.m. Please express to Mr. Sandler our deep
                    appreciation for his courtesy in making this information available to us and say
                    that the interest of the United States Government in the reduction and
                    limitation of armaments has in no way abated.</p>
                <p>Repeat to Bern by mail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
